<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
<title>Night Dice — Help &amp; Support</title>
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #223843;
    --card: rgba(239,241,243,0.06);
    --line: rgba(219,211,216,0.18);
    --ink: #EFF1F3;
    --muted: #DBD3D8;
    --accent: #D77A61;
    --sand: #D8B4A0;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body {
    margin: 0;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.6;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  .wrap { max-width: 740px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 48px 22px 80px; }
  header { margin-bottom: 28px; }
  .brand { font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: 2px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--muted); }
  .brand b { color: var(--accent); }
  h1 { font-size: 30px; font-weight: 800; margin: 14px 0 6px; }
  .sub { color: var(--sand); font-size: 16px; }
  h2 { font-size: 20px; margin: 36px 0 10px; }
  h3 { font-size: 16px; margin: 18px 0 4px; color: var(--sand); }
  p, li { color: var(--ink); }
  a { color: var(--accent); }
  ul, ol { padding-left: 20px; }
  li { margin: 6px 0; }
  .card {
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    margin: 14px 0;
  }
  .faq h3 { margin-top: 0; }
  .pill {
    display: inline-block;
    background: rgba(215,122,97,0.18);
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 700; font-size: 13px;
    border-radius: 999px; padding: 4px 12px; margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .steps li { margin: 8px 0; }
  footer { margin-top: 48px; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); padding-top: 18px; color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; }
  footer a { color: var(--sand); }
</style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <header>
      <div class="brand">NIGHT <b>DICE</b></div>
      <h1>Help &amp; Support</h1>
      <div class="sub">Rules and a scorekeeper for classic dice games.</div>
    </header>

    <h2>Getting started</h2>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li><strong>Pick a game</strong> from the home screen — each card shows the
      players and number of variations.</li>
      <li><strong>Read the rules</strong> any time with the book icon, or from the
      <em>Rules</em> button on the home screen.</li>
      <li><strong>Start a game:</strong> add players (names are optional — blank slots
      become "Player 1," "Player 2," and so on), choose a variation, then tap
      <em>Start Game</em>.</li>
      <li><strong>Keep score:</strong> most games use quick +/− buttons with a running
      total; Yard Dice and Bunco use a tap-to-enter scorecard that totals automatically.</li>
      <li><strong>Finish</strong> to crown a winner and save the game to your History.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

    <div class="card faq">
      <h3>Do I need an internet connection?</h3>
      <p>No. Night Dice works completely offline.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card faq">
      <h3>Where is my data stored? Is any of it sent anywhere?</h3>
      <p>Everything — player names, scores, and saved games — is stored only on your
      device and is never transmitted. See our
      <a href="privacy.html">Privacy Policy</a> for details.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card faq">
      <h3>Can I pause a game and come back to it?</h3>
      <p>Yes. Your in-progress game is saved automatically. When you return to the home
      screen, tap <em>Resume Game</em> to pick up where you left off. Starting a brand-new
      game will replace the one in progress.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card faq">
      <h3>How do I delete my saved games?</h3>
      <p>Open <em>History</em> and remove individual games, discard an in-progress game
      from the Resume card, or delete the app to remove all data at once.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card faq">
      <h3>Are these the "official" rules?</h3>
      <p>The rules are original, plain-language summaries written to help you play. They
      are not affiliated with, endorsed by, or copied from any game publisher. House rules
      vary widely — agree on yours before you start, and use the in-app variations as a
      guide.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card faq">
      <h3>One game needs special equipment — why?</h3>
      <p>Bounce Die is a toss-and-catch board game that uses a dedicated board and a
      specialty bounce die (sold as a set). The app keeps score; you supply the gear.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card faq">
      <h3>Why is the app rated for older audiences?</h3>
      <p>Some traditional games reference alcohol as the stakes (for example, deciding who
      buys the next round). The app itself only keeps score.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Play responsibly</h2>
    <p class="card">Several games in Night Dice come from bar and party traditions. If your
    group chooses to play with drinks, please do so responsibly and only where it is legal
    for everyone involved. Never drink and drive. The non-drinking framing and "set your own
    stakes" options work just as well.</p>

    <h2>Contact us</h2>
    <p>Need help, found a bug, or have a suggestion? Email
    <a href="mailto:bideapp@gmail.com">bideapp@gmail.com</a> and we'll get back to you.</p>

    <footer>
      Night Dice is an unofficial scorekeeping and rules-reference app. Game names are used
      descriptively to identify traditional games; any trademarks belong to their respective
      owners. &nbsp;·&nbsp; <a href="privacy.html">Privacy Policy</a>
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
